---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy">
  <main class="container-custom py-10 sm:py-16">
    {/* Header */}
    <header class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >

        <h1
          class="mt-2 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-navy"
        >
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>

        <div
          class="mt-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-2 text-sm text-gray-500"
        >
          <span class="hidden sm:inline">•</span>
          <a
            href="mailto:support@protize.com"
            class="text-primary underline underline-offset-4"
          >
            support@protize.com
          </a>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-5 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>Protize</strong> (“we”, “us”,
          “our”) collects, uses, shares, and safeguards information in connection
          with our website, products, and services (the “Services”). By using our
          Services, you agree to the practices described here.
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Quick navigation */}
      <nav
        class="mt-6 rounded-2xl  p-4 sm:p-5 "
      >
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3">Quick links</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {
            [
              ["#info", "Information We Collect"],
              ["#use", "How We Use Information"],
              ["#share", "How We Share Information"],
              ["#cookies", "Cookies"],
              ["#rights", "Your Rights"],
              ["#contact", "Contact"],
            ].map(([href, label]) => (
              <a
                href={href}
                class="rounded-full border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-100 hover:text-black transition"
              >
                {label}
              </a>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </nav>
    </header>

    {/* Content */}
    <div class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-4xl space-y-6">
      <section
        id="info"
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">1) Information We Collect</h2>

        <div class="mt-4 space-y-5 text-gray-700">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">
              A. Information you provide to us
            </h3>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong>Account details</strong> (name, email, password), if you
                sign up or contact us.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Business information</strong> you share when requesting proposals,
                demos, or support.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Content and files</strong> you upload or send to us (e.g.,
                attachments, messages, form inputs).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Billing details</strong> (handled by our payment processors—Protize
                doesn’t store full card numbers).
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">
              B. Information collected automatically
            </h3>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong>Log data</strong>: IP address, browser/OS, referring
                URLs, pages visited, timestamps, and error logs.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Device & usage data</strong>: interactions with pages
                and features for performance and reliability.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Cookies / localStorage</strong>: to remember
                preferences, enable core functionality, and measure usage.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">
              C. Information from third parties
            </h3>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>
                Authentication providers (e.g., OAuth SSO) if you use them to
                log in.
              </li>
              <li>
                Analytics, monitoring, and support tools that help us run our
                Services.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section
        id="use"
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">2) How We Use Information</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>Provide, operate, and improve the Services.</li>
          <li>Personalize content and experiences, where applicable.</li>
          <li>
            Communicate with you about updates, security alerts, and
            administrative messages.
          </li>
          <li>Respond to inquiries and provide customer support.</li>
          <li>
            Monitor reliability, troubleshoot issues, and prevent fraud, abuse,
            or security incidents.
          </li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce agreements.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">3) Legal Bases (EEA/UK)</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Where applicable, we process personal data on these bases: (i)
          performance of a contract; (ii) legitimate interests (e.g., securing
          and improving Services); (iii) consent (e.g., certain
          cookies/marketing); and (iv) compliance with legal obligations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        id="share"
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">
          4) How We Share Information
        </h2>

        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>
            <strong>Service providers</strong> that help us host, analyze, deliver
            emails, process payments, and provide support.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Business transfers</strong> in the event of a merger, acquisition,
            or reorganization.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal reasons</strong> to meet applicable laws, regulations,
            or lawful requests.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Aggregated or de-identified data</strong> that does not identify
            you.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div
          class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 text-sm text-gray-700"
        >
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Common processors we may use
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Hosting/CDN & infrastructure (e.g., cloud providers)</li>
            <li>
              Analytics & monitoring (e.g., privacy-respecting analytics, error
              tracking)
            </li>
            <li>Email delivery and customer support tooling</li>
            <li>Payment processing (if you purchase services)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We will provide a current list of sub-processors upon request.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section
        id="cookies"
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">
          5) Cookies & Similar Technologies
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We use essential cookies for authentication and security, and optional
          cookies for analytics and performance. You can control cookies through
          your browser settings. Some features may not function properly without
          essential cookies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">6) Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We retain personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes
          above, to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce
          agreements. When data is no longer needed, we delete or anonymize it
          using reasonable measures.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">7) Security</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We employ industry-standard safeguards (e.g., TLS in transit, access
          controls). No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure; we
          cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">8) International Transfers</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          If you access the Services from outside the country where we host or
          process data, your information may be transferred internationally. We
          implement appropriate safeguards for such transfers where required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        id="rights"
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">9) Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct,
          update, delete, or restrict the processing of your personal data; to
          data portability; and to object to certain processing. You may also
          withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          To exercise rights, contact us at
          <a
            href="mailto:support@protize.com"
            class="text-primary underline underline-offset-4"
            >support@protize.com</a
          >. We may need to verify your identity to respond.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">
          10) Additional Disclosures for California Residents
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          If you are a California resident, you have rights under the CCPA/CPRA,
          including the right to know, delete, correct, and opt out of certain
          disclosures. We do not “sell” personal information as defined by the
          CCPA/CPRA.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">
          12) Third-Party Sites & Services
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Our website may contain links to third-party websites or services.
          Their privacy practices are governed by their own policies. We
          encourage you to review those policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">13) Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the
          updated version with a revised “Last updated” date, and for material
          changes, we may provide additional notice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        id="contact"
        class="rounded-2xl  "
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy">14) Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          For questions, requests, or complaints regarding this Privacy Policy
          or your personal data, contact:
        </p>

        <div
          class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 text-gray-700"
        >
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Protize</p>
          <p class="mt-1">
            Email:
            <a
              href="mailto:support@protize.com"
              class="text-primary underline underline-offset-4"
            >
              support@protize.com
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <aside
        class="rounded-2xl  text-sm text-gray-600 "
      >
        <p>
          <strong>Note:</strong> This policy is a general template tailored for Protize’s
          typical website and services. Your actual data flows, vendors, and jurisdictions
          may require updates. Please consult legal counsel for compliance with laws
          applicable to your business (e.g., GDPR, CPRA, India DPDP Act).
        </p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
